  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "У вас есть...? — the shop question",
    "explanation": "**У вас есть...?** is the single most useful phrase for any shop, market, or pharmacy: \"Do you have...?\" (formal/plural — вы, genitive of вы is **вас**). It's the exact same pattern as **у тебя есть**, just with вас instead of тебя.\n\n**У вас есть хлеб?** works whether you're asking one shopkeeper or a whole counter of them.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "У вас есть хлеб?", "en": "Do you have bread?" },
      { "ru": "У вас есть свежий хлеб?", "en": "Do you have fresh bread?" },
      { "ru": "У вас есть размер...?", "en": "Do you have the size...?" },
      { "ru": "Да, есть. Вот, пожалуйста.", "en": "Yes, we do. Here you go." }
    ]
  },

